(1583, 199, 'company_faq_company_faq_question_&_ans_0_question_ans', '<h4>Q1- How do we sign up to SCM?</h4>\r\nWhilst on the home page, simply select which membership type you are best suited, whether you are a company or a subcontractor, just follow the simple steps to sign in. If you need any more help or advice, please visit our contact us page and we will advise the best plan for you.\r\n<h4>Q2- Can we preview subcontractors before becoming a member?</h4>\r\nYou are able to do a search using the home page and the platform will let you know how many subcontractors that meet your search criteria are available on that day, however you will not be able to access their profiles or use any of the search sorting tools. Keep in mind, this is a LIVE database, so each time you search the results can change depending on subcontractor’s availability. One day you may have 22 available, the next there could be 2..\r\n<h4>Q3- How do I know if/ when a subcontractor is available?</h4>\r\nOnly subcontractor that are available will show in the results of any search. This saves wasting anytime making contact or sending booking requests to subcontractors that are not available or are unlikely to respond because they are busy and their contact details are just simply listed on a directory.\r\n<h4>Q4- Is there a limit on the number of subcontractors we can view and hire?</h4>\r\nThere is no limit to the number of subcontractors we can view or hire. The platform is not simply a directory you are subscribing to access, it’s a live database so from day to day, even minute to mute the results will change depending on subcontractor’s availability and your own search criteria.\r\n<h4>Q5- Can we contact the subcontractor directly through the site?</h4>\r\nYou are able to submit a booking request at the click of a button which will automatically the notify the subcontractor and enable them to accept or if they are still available for those dates. Once accepted you can contact them in whichever way you’d prefer and make arrangements as you would normally.\r\n<h4>Q6- Once I have made contact or booked a subcontractor are we able to continue to use them?</h4>\r\nComing Soon\r\n<h4>Q7- How do we guarantee the quality of work by the subcontractors?</h4>\r\nThe subcontractors profiles are very comprehensive when it comes to giving the right and enough information so as an employer/company you can decide if you would like to make contact. The platform has a badge system which enables you to breakdown a search based on experience to manage expectations and each profile also has a 5 star rating system so you can a feel from previous contracts.\r\n<h4>Q8- Can we hire whole teams or just individuals?</h4>\r\nYou can hire whole teams or individuals. The platforms intelligent sorting feature enables you to sort either at the top of your search results. There is a team icon shown for subcontractors that also employ others so as to undertake larger projects. The profiles appear differently for these subcontractor’s so as you are able to essentially ‘meet the team’ and better understand the typical contracts they undertake prior to sending a booking request.\r\n<h4>Q9- How does the badge system work?</h4>\r\nThere are 3 badge options given to each subcontractor which is clearly displayed on their profile and can be used to sort any searches. The Badge options are labourer, trainee and tradesman.\r\n<h4>Q10- How does the different levels/ types of membership work</h4>\r\nFor Companies, the membership options are split into bronze, silver and gold depending on the work radius you cover/would like to search.\r\n<h4>Q11- Can we have multiple devices?</h4>\r\nComing Soon'),
