(1595, 199, 'sub_contractor_faq_sub_contractor_faq_question_&_ans_0_question_ans', '<h4>Q1 – How do I sign up to Subcontract me?</h4>\r\nWhilst on the home page, simply select which membership type you are best suited, whether you are a company or a subcontractor, just follow the simple steps to sign in. If you need any more help or advice, please visit our contact us page.\r\n<h4>Q2 – Why would I subscribe to SCM rather than checkatrade or another construction directory?</h4>\r\nSCM is not just a trade directory for customers, SCM is an intelligent tool enabling you or your company to be a part of a live database. Unlike other trade membership sites which are primarily focused towards domestic customers, SCM is specifically targated at the commercial market connecting companies with subcontractors based on their availability and skillset.\r\n<h4>Q3- Before I sign up can I preview what jobs are available to me?</h4>\r\nOur platform doesn’t not display available jobs.  The platform is designed for companies to be able to see available subcontractors live at a click of a button in line with their search criteria. As a subcontractor you are able to manage your own availability and visibility using the platforms clever calender tool.\r\n<h4>Q4 – how do I make sure my profile is being viewed?</h4>\r\nOur intelligent software will prioritise profiles 1<sup>st</sup> by availability and then by last updated. If you want to stay on top, then be sure to keep your profile updated regularly starting with your availability.\r\n<h4>Q5 – How do I get the best result from my profile?</h4>\r\nBe sure to keep your profile updated and accurate in terms of availability, make sure your profile clearly and accurately shows the services and experience you are offering. Then get out there with some great work and build those ratings. As your profile builds, so will your reputation and therefore the amount of work available to you.\r\n<h4>Q6- How does the badge system work?</h4>\r\nThe badge system is a quick visual indicator to companies showing your experience level or stage at which you are in your career. There are 3 badge options given when creating your profile, they are labourer, trainee or tradesmen. We advise this is shown accurately as this platform unlike any other platform gives labourers and trainees the chance to kick start their careers, build a profile, grow their network and all at their own pace.\r\n<h4><strong>Q7 – How does the booking system work?</strong></h4>\r\nYour profile has a live colour coded calendar in the top right which enables you to easily to block out anytime you are not available. Once you have blocked a date as unavailable, your profile will not appear in any company searches. Any dates you haven’t blocked out will automatically show as available so as companies are able to find you and send you a booking request. There is also a quick toggle at the top you can slide to on or off enabling you to quickly turn your visibility off if required. You will be able to accept or decline any booking requests directly from the notification panel.\r\n<h4>Q8- am I able to make contact with the company directly?</h4>\r\nYou will not be able to contact a company directly via this platform until they have sent you a booking request.\r\n<h4>Q9- Can the company rate me.  What If they think I’ve done a bad job?</h4>\r\nYes a company is able to rate you using our 5 star rating system. If a subcontractor receives a rating under three stars more than once this will be flagged to our admin team who will then make contact with the company to understand the reason and see if this rating can be improved.\r\n<h4><strong>Q10- Can a subcontractor be removed from Subcontractme?</strong></h4>\r\nSubcontract me reserves the right to cancel any members subscription if necessary.  A subscription will only be considered for cancellation through non-payment or if a subcontractor has received a less than 3 star rating on three or more occasions.'),
