(1603, 199, 'sub_contractor_faq_sub_contractor_faq_question_&_ans_2_question_ans', '<h4>Q11 - Can I dispute a rating?</h4>\r\nWe understand that not all jobs go to plan but we wouldn’t advise you dispute a rating with a company directly.  Instead contact our help team and we will make contact with the company on your behalf to better understand the rating and if there is anything that can be done to improve it.\r\n<h4>Q12 - Can a subcontractor be removed from Subcontractme?</h4>\r\nSubcontract me reserves the right to cancel any members subscription if necessary.  A subscription will only be considered for cancellation through non-payment or if a subcontractor has received a less than 3 star rating on three or more occasions\r\n<h4>Q13- If it doesn’t work for me can I cancel my subscription at anytime?</h4>\r\nYes, you can cancel at any time.  Your subscription will be cancelled at the start of the following calender month.  Subscriptions can be paused should your reason be a financial one. Before cancelling your subscription please talk to one of our team members as we may be able to help you get more out of your subscription.\r\n<h4>Q14 – How do I cancel my subscription?</h4>\r\nComing Soon'),
